= SDL_RenderLines =
Use this function to draw a series of connected lines on the current rendering target.


== Syntax ==
```c++
int SDL_RenderLines(const SDL_Point* points,
                    int              count)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''points'''
|the points along the lines
|-
|'''count'''
|the number of points, drawing count-1 lines
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns 0 on success or -1 if there is no rendering context current; call [[SDL_GetError]]() for more information.

